Title: Note on the point-splitting procedure to evaluate vacuum fluctuation in
  certain cylindrically symmetric backgrounds
Authors: I. Brevik, G.E.A. Matsas and E.S. Moreira Jr
Comments: REVTeX file, 7 pages
Report-no: IFT-P.020/98
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D58 (1998) 027502
\\
  We revisit two-point function approaches used to study vacuum fluctuation in
wedge-shaped regions and conical backgrounds. Appearance of divergent integrals
is discussed and circumvented. The issue is considered in the context of a
massless scalar field in cosmic string spacetime.
